\item $f_*\mathcal O_X(nM)$ is 
locally free for $n \gg 0$ sufficiently divisible; and

\item $\operatorname{det} f'_*\mathcal O_{X'}(nM')$ is nef for $n \gg 0$ sufficiently divisible.
\end{enumerate}


Then for all $n \gg 0$ sufficiently divisible and $k > 0$ we have
isomorphisms
 $\beta^*\operatorname{det} f_*\mathcal O_X(nM) \cong \operatorname{det} f'_*\mathcal O_{X'}(nM')$.  Moreover, if $p\colon W \rightarrow X$ and $q\colon W \rightarrow X'$
 resolves the rational map $X' \dashrightarrow X$ we have 
$q^*(kM'+(f')^*c_1(\operatorname{det} f'_*\mathcal O_{X'}(nM'))) \sim_{\mathbb Q} p^*(kM+f^*c_1(\operatorname{det} f_*\mathcal O_X(nM)))$.

